{"lemma":"كَبْرَةُ","slug":"كَبْرَةُ","root":"ك.ب.ر","root_slug":"ك-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36574","n36575","n36576","n36577"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36574","headword_ar":"كَبْرَةٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabira","text_ar":"كَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Oldness; age; old age;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K; *) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaburapN","text_ar":"كَبُرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makobarapN","text_ar":"مَكْبَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makburapN","text_ar":"مَكبُرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makobirN","text_ar":"مَكْبِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kibarN","text_ar":"كِبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The last two, the latter of which is the most common of all, are inf. ns. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabira","text_ar":"كَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealatohu kaburapN","text_ar":"عَلَتْهُ كَبُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaburapN","text_ar":"كَبُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mukobarapN","text_ar":"مُكْبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makoburapN","text_ar":"مَكْبُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAhu Almakobiru","text_ar":"عَلَاهُ المَكْبِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makobirN","text_ar":"مَكْبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kibarN","text_ar":"كِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Age overcame him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advanced in age."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealatohu kaborapN","text_ar":"عَلَتْهُ كَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said, tropically, of a sword, and of the iron head or blade of a weapon, when it has become old: (TA:) or of an old iron head or blade of a weapon when spoilt by rust. (M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaborapN","text_ar":"كَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used by AHn with respect to dates and the like. (L.) [See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaloqapN","text_ar":"حَلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n36575","headword_ar":"كِبْرَةٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabiyrapN","text_ar":"كَبِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kiboratuhumo","text_ar":"هُوَ كِبْرَتُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubur~atuhumo","text_ar":"كُبُرَّتُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, K,) so in the handwriting of AHeyth., (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikobir~atuhumo","text_ar":"اـِكْبِرَّتُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobir~atuhumo","text_ar":"اَكْبِرَّتُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuboruhumo","text_ar":"كُبْرُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubur~uhumo","text_ar":"كُبُرُّهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the greatest of them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in headship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is the nearest of them in kin to his chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oldest, ancestor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his intermediate ancestors being fewer in number:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) but some of these epithets are differently explained, as follows:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA kiborapu A^abiyhi","text_ar":"هٰذَا كِبْرَةُ اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is the greatest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oldest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the children of his father; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sigorapu A^abiyhi","text_ar":"صِغْرَةُ اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kiborapu","text_ar":"هُوَ كِبْرَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladi A^abawayohi","text_ar":"وَلَدِ اَبَوَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is the greatest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oldest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akbr","text_ar":"اكبر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the children of his parents:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, Az:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is the last of the children of his parents;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, S;) and the like is said of a female, (Sh, ISk, S,) and of a pl. number: (ISk, S:) it is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eijozapu waladi A^abawayohi","text_ar":"عِجْزَةُ وَلَدِ اَبَوَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sh, A'Obeyd, S:) or, accord. to Ks and Az, this last phrase has this meaning; but Az says, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborap","text_ar":"كِبْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"means otherwise, namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A_ikobir~apu qawomihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اـِكْبِرَّةُ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is the greatest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oldest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like is said of a female, and of a pl. number: (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomihi","text_ar":"قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kuboru","text_ar":"هُوَ كُبْرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomihi","text_ar":"قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomihi","text_ar":"قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukobur~u","text_ar":"اُكْبُرُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufoEul~","text_ar":"اُفْعُلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and applied to a woman as to a man, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is the nearest of his people in kin to his chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oldest, ancestor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) in which sense,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomihi","text_ar":"قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna kubora","text_ar":"كَانَ كُبْرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of El-'Abbás, in a trad., because there remained not, in his lifetime, any one of the descendants of Háshim more nearly related to him than he: (L:) and in another trad. it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlawlA='u llkubori","text_ar":"الَولا=ءُ للكُبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the right to the inheritance of the property left by an emancipated slave belongs to the nearest in kin"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the emancipater"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sons of the emancipater;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) i. e., when a man [who has emancipated a slave] dies, leaving a son and a grandson, the right to the inheritance of the property left by the emancipated slave belongs to the son, not the grandson. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Az","TA","A","Ks","Sh","ISk","S","L","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n36576","headword_ar":"كَبُرَةٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaborapN","text_ar":"كَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n36577","headword_ar":"كُبُرَّةٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborapN","text_ar":"كِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}